  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Due Diligence in Metallurgic Supply Chains</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Three companies will execute this project: Tata Steel, LDM and Hunter Douglas.All three are members of VNMI that intends to sign an IMVO convenant.In general, VNMI members use metal ores / concentrates, secondary metals / metal scrap and semi manufactured metal products. These products are partly sourced from countries where child labour may be an issue. The first step of this project entails the selection of at least 2 specific supply chains and countries that will be the focus for the project. The root causes of child labour in these supply chains will be analysed in this project, including mitigating measures to address these and taking into account the companies&#x2019; responsibilities within the UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights (UNGP). In addition, current internal operational processes will be reviewed and if necessary adjusted (action plans for implementation will be developed). Based on the lessons learned from this project a tailored child labour tool kit will be developed that will be made available to other VNMI members and other interested parties.</narrative>
  </description>
